    [2m- **Node.js `node --test` test script.** `node --test test` is interpreted by Node as a test-name pattern, NOT a dir[22m
[2m[39;120Hrectory. To run tests in a `test/` or `tests/` directory write the script as `node --test test/` (trailing slash) or with[22m
[2m[39;120Hh a glob: `node --test 'test/**/*.test.js'`. Verify by running the script before declaring success.[22m[K
    [2m- **Test commands from `package.json scripts.test`.** The orchestrator runs the workspace's declared `test` script d[22m
[2m[39;120Hduring Phase 9.2. If your script can't actually invoke the tests you wrote, Phase 9.2 reports zero suites and the Phase G[22m
[2m[39;120HGate fails. Run `npm test` locally as part of your verification step before the final summary — never claim "tests pass" [22m
[2m[39;120H without having seen them pass.[22m[K
    [2m- **Frontend / backend technology drift.** Active constraints carry the project's declared stack (e.g. SvelteKit, Bu[22m
